title: Spicy Shrimp Cakes with Corn and Avocado Salsa
summary: The recipe Spicy Shrimp Cakes with Corn and Avocado Salsa could satisfy your Mexican craving in about 45 minutes. For $1.34 per serving, you get a hor d'oeuvre that serves 10. Watching your figure? This dairy free and pescatarian recipe has 123 calories, 11g of protein, and 4g of fat per serving. 1 person found this recipe to be scrumptious and satisfying. A mixture of hot sauce, green onions, lime juice, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so delicious. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 38%. This score is not so super. Similar recipes are Cheesy Corn Cakes with Spicy Avocado Salsa, Corn cakes with avocado salsa, and Jalapeno Corn Cakes with Avocado Salsa.

winePairing.pairingText: Pinot Grigio, Riesling, and Sauvignon Blanc are my top picks for Shrimp. These crisp white wines work well with shrimp prepared in a variety of ways, whether grilled, fried, or in garlic sauce. The Tiamo Pinot Grigio with a 4.4 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 11 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: Tiamo Pinot Grigio
productMatches.description: Light straw yellow color. Fresh and rich fruity aromas of apple and pear with a hint of citrus fruit that fade into the floral bouquet. Fresh and fruity, very clean and crisp.Tiamo Pinot Grigio pairs well with a wide array of lighter cuisine, especially fish/shellfish, poultry, pastas in cream sauce and softer cheeses. It's also an ideal aperitif.

instructions: To prepare cakes, place shrimp in a food processor; pulse 10 times or until finely chopped. Set aside.                                                                                                Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Coat pan with cooking spray. Add bell pepper to pan; saut 3 minutes. Add garlic to pan; saut for 1 minute. Remove from heat. Place bell pepper mixture in a large bowl. Add shrimp, green onions, and the next 6 ingredients (through egg), stirring well. Stir in cilantro and 1/4 cup panko.                                                                                                Divide shrimp mixture into 10 equal portions, shaping each portion into a 1/2-inch-thick patty. Dredge both sides of patties in remaining 1/2 cup panko. Chill at least one hour.                                                                                                Heat pan over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray. Add 5 cakes to pan; cook 4 minutes on each side or until browned. Remove from pan; cover and keep warm. Repeat procedure with remaining cakes.                                                                                                To prepare salsa, combine corn and remaining ingredients; stir gently. Serve immediately with shrimp cakes.

steps.step: To prepare cakes, place shrimp in a food processor; pulse 10 times or until finely chopped. Set aside.
Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Coat pan with cooking spray.
Add bell pepper to pan; saut 3 minutes.
Add garlic to pan; saut for 1 minute.
Place bell pepper mixture in a large bowl.
Add shrimp, green onions, and the next 6 ingredients (through egg), stirring well. Stir in cilantro and 1/4 cup panko.
Divide shrimp mixture into 10 equal portions, shaping each portion into a 1/2-inch-thick patty. Dredge both sides of patties in remaining 1/2 cup panko. Chill at least one hour.
Heat pan over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray.
Add 5 cakes to pan; cook 4 minutes on each side or until browned.
Remove from pan; cover and keep warm. Repeat procedure with remaining cakes.
To prepare salsa, combine corn and remaining ingredients; stir gently.
